  "prompt": "How do I use WhatsApp on a PC?",
  "response": "There are a few ways to use WhatsApp on your PC:\n\n**1. WhatsApp Web (Browser-Based):**\n\n*   **How it works:** This is the most common and easiest method. It mirrors your WhatsApp account from your phone to your computer browser.  Your phone *must* be connected to the internet for WhatsApp Web to function.\n*   **Steps:**\n    1.  **On your PC:** Open your web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari, etc.) and go to web.whatsapp.com.  You'll see a QR code displayed.\n    2.  **On your phone (with WhatsApp installed):**\n        *   **Android:** Tap the three dots in the upper right corner of the WhatsApp app, then select \"Linked devices.\"\n        *   **iPhone:**  Tap \"Settings\" at the bottom right of the WhatsApp app, then select \"Linked Devices.\"\n    3.  **On your phone:** Tap \"Link a device\" (or \"Link Device\").  You might need to use your fingerprint, Face ID, or phone PIN to verify your identity.\n    4.  **On your phone:** Point your phone's camera at the QR code displayed on your PC's web browser.  The camera will automatically scan the code.\n    5.  **On your PC:** WhatsApp will now load in your browser.\n\n*   **Pros:**\n    *   No installation needed.\n    *   Works on any operating system with a web browser.\n    *   Easy to set up.\n\n*   **Cons:**\n    *   Your phone must be connected to the internet. If your phone loses connection, WhatsApp Web will disconnect.\n    *   Can be slightly slower than the desktop app.\n\n**2. WhatsApp Desktop App (Standalone Application):**\n\n*   **How it works:** This is a standalone application you download and install on your computer.  Like WhatsApp Web, it mirrors your account from your phone, and your phone needs to be connected to the internet.\n*   **Steps:**\n    1.  **On your PC:** Go to the WhatsApp download page: whatsapp.com/download\n    2.  **Download:**  Choose the appropriate version for your operating system (Windows or macOS).\n    3.  **Install:** Run the downloaded installer and follow the on-screen instructions.\n    4.  **Open WhatsApp:**  Launch the WhatsApp application. You will see a QR code.\n    5.  **On your phone (with WhatsApp installed):**\n        *   **Android:** Tap the three dots in the upper right corner of the WhatsApp app, then select \"Linked devices.\"\n        *   **iPhone:**  Tap \"Settings\" at the bottom right of the WhatsApp app, then select \"Linked Devices.\"\n    6.  **On your phone:** Tap \"Link a device\" (or \"Link Device\"). You might need to use your fingerprint, Face ID, or phone PIN to verify your identity.\n    7.  **On your phone:** Point your phone's camera at the QR code displayed on your PC's WhatsApp application.\n    8.  **On your PC:** WhatsApp will now load in the desktop application.\n\n*   **Pros:**\n    *   Dedicated application; potentially more stable than WhatsApp Web.\n    *   Offers desktop notifications.\n    *   May be slightly faster than the web version.\n\n*   **Cons:**\n    *   Requires installation.\n    *   Your phone must be connected to the internet.  If your phone loses connection, the desktop app will disconnect.\n    *   Only available for Windows and macOS.\n\n**Important Considerations for Both Methods:**\n\n*   **Phone Connection:**  As mentioned repeatedly, *your phone needs to be connected to the internet for either WhatsApp Web or the desktop app to work.*  They are not independent applications.\n*   **Battery Life:** Using WhatsApp on your PC still relies on your phone processing the messages.  This can drain your phone's battery faster.\n*   **Security:** Always log out of WhatsApp Web or the desktop app when you're finished, especially on shared computers, to prevent unauthorized access to your account.  From your phone's WhatsApp app, under \"Linked Devices\", you can see all linked devices and log out remotely.\n*   **Account Linking:** You can link multiple devices to your WhatsApp account, so you can use WhatsApp Web on your home computer and the desktop app on your work computer simultaneously.\n\n**Troubleshooting:**\n\n*   **QR Code Issues:**  Make sure your phone's camera is clean and has good lighting.  Ensure the QR code is fully visible on your computer screen.  Restart your phone and/or computer if you're having trouble.\n*   **Connectivity Issues:** Check your internet connection on both your phone and computer.  Restart your router if necessary.\n*   **Outdated WhatsApp:** Ensure you have the latest version of WhatsApp installed on your phone.\n*   **Firewall/Antivirus:**  Sometimes, firewall or antivirus software can block WhatsApp Web or the desktop app.  Temporarily disable them to see if that's the issue (then re-enable them and configure exceptions for WhatsApp if needed).\n*   **Browser Cache:** Clear your browser's cache and cookies if you're having issues with WhatsApp Web.\n\nChoose the method that best suits your needs and remember that a phone with a working WhatsApp account is required.\n",
